      • Acute Kidney Injury AKI
      • Cohort Entry Events
      • Inclusion Criteria
        • 1. Washout period with no AKI codes: To rule out diagnosis codes that are follow ups (for example: check for status of recovery or progression, check sequelae, etc) from the actual event of AKI
        • 2. No ESKD at baseline: To exclude cases with a diagnosis of End-Stage Kidney Disease in the 365 days before AKI occurrence. Period from -365 to -7 to account for ESKD due to the index episode of AKI
        • 3. No chronic dialysis at baseline (-365 to 8 days) : To exclude all patients receiving chronic dialysis defined as more than 3 recorded events of dialysis in the 1 year- 8 days before index date, or one erythropoietin dose and dialysis in same year
        • 4. No Kidney Transplant any time prior

ABREVIATIONS

DATA SOURCES

The data sources used in this analysis will be determined empirically by evaluating the study inputs against pre-computed characterization results. This method generates a rough estimate determining which databases have the information necessary to observe both the outcomes and exposures of interest in the required populations. Only databases that pass data diagnostics will be used in the study.

Acute Kidney Injury AKI

Cohort Entry Events

People may enter the cohort when observing any of the following:

  1. condition occurrences of âAcute kidney injury (Narrow definition)â.

  2. procedure occurrences of âDialysis procedure at a Medicare certified ESRD facility for acute kidney injury without ESRDâ.

Inclusion Criteria

1. Washout period with no AKI codes: To rule out diagnosis codes that are follow ups (for example: check for status of recovery or progression, check sequelae, etc) from the actual event of AKI

Entry events with all of the following criteria:

  1. having no condition occurrences of âAcute kidney injury (Narrow definition)â, starting in the 30 days prior to cohort entry start date; allow events outside observation period.
  2. having no procedure occurrences of âDialysis procedure at a Medicare certified ESRD facility for acute kidney injury without ESRDâ, starting in the 30 days prior to cohort entry start date; allow events outside observation period.

2. No ESKD at baseline: To exclude cases with a diagnosis of End-Stage Kidney Disease in the 365 days before AKI occurrence. Period from -365 to -7 to account for ESKD due to the index episode of AKI

Entry events having no condition occurrences of âEnd-stage renal diseaseâ, starting between 365 days before and 7 days before cohort entry start date; allow events outside observation period.

3. No chronic dialysis at baseline (-365 to 8 days) : To exclude all patients receiving chronic dialysis defined as more than 3 recorded events of dialysis in the 1 year- 8 days before index date, or one erythropoietin dose and dialysis in same year

Entry events with any of the following criteria:

  1. having at most 3 procedure occurrences of âDialysisâ, starting between 365 days before and 8 days before cohort entry start date; allow events outside observation period.

  2. with all of the following criteria:

    1. having no procedure occurrences of âDialysisâ, starting between 365 days before and 8 days before cohort entry start date; allow events outside observation period.
    2. having no drug exposures of âErythropoietin like drugsâ, starting between 365 days before and 8 days before cohort entry start date; allow events outside observation period.

4. No Kidney Transplant any time prior

Entry events with all of the following criteria:

  1. having no condition occurrences of âKidney transplantconditionsâ, starting anytime on or before cohort entry start date; allow events outside observation period.
  2. having no procedure occurrences of âKidney transplant procedureâ, starting anytime on or before cohort entry start date; allow events outside observation period.

Cohort Exit

The cohort end date will be offset from index eventâs end date plus 0 days.

Cohort Eras

Entry events will be combined into cohort eras if they are within 0 days of each other.
